2.9. Your responsibility in the event of misuse of your card
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
2.9.1 In the event that the card has been misused by another
person, &BANKNAVN. will cover the loss unless said loss is
covered by Articles 2.9.2-2.9.6. It is &BANKNAVN. that must prove
that the loss is covered by Articles 2.9.1-2.9.6.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.9.2 If your card and PIN code have been misused by another
person, you will be required to cover losses of up to DKK 1,100. You
will not be required to pay more than DKK 1,100 in total if
several of your cards with the same PIN code are misused in
connection with the same incident. However, this is conditional
upon you blocking all cards at the same time.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.9.3 You will be required to cover losses up to DKK 8,000 in the
event that your card has been misused by another person and the PIN
code has been used, and
.of 5mm
-¤you have failed to inform &BANKNAVN. without delay after realising
that you had lost your card, or that unauthorised persons had become
aware of the associated code,
.of
.of 5mm
-¤you have disclosed the code to the person who carried out the
unauthorised use, and you did not realise - or could not reasonably
have been expected to realise - that there was a risk of misuse, or
.of
.of 5mm
-¤you have facilitated the unauthorised use through grossly
irresponsible behaviour.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
In total, you have to pay a maximum of 8,000 Danish kroner if more of your
cards with the same PIN code have been exploited fraudulently in connection
with the same event.
This, however, implies that all cards with the same PIN code have been
blocked at the same time.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.9.4 You will be required to cover losses up to DKK 8,000 in the
event that your card has been misused by another person, when your
card has been read physically or electronically, and the unauthorised
person has used a false signature in connection with the use, and
.of 5mm
-¤that you or a party to whom you have transferred the card, have
failed to inform &BANKNAVN. without undue delay after becoming aware
that the card had been lost, or
.of
.of 5mm
-¤you or any other person to whom you have given the card has
facilitated the unauthorised use through grossly irresponsible
behaviour.
.of
.sp 3mm
Your total liability cannot exceed DKK 8,000 even if you are held
liable pursuant to both Article 2.9.3 and Article 2.9.4. You will not
be required to pay more than DKK 8,000 in total if several of your
cards with the same PIN code have been misused in connection with the
same incident. However, this is conditional upon you blocking all
cards with the same PIN code at the same time.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.9.5 You will be held liable for the full amount if your PIN code has
been used in connection with the misuse under the following conditions:
.of 5mm
-¤You have revealed the PIN code to the person who misused the card and
realised or should have realised that there was a risk of misuse.
.of
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.9.6 You will also be held liable for the full amount if you have acted
fraudulently or have intentionally failed to fulfil your
obligations according to the regulations, including keeping the
card and the mobile phone for MasterCard SecureCode in a safe
place(see clause 2.3), protecting the PIN code (see clause 2.4) or
blocking the card (see clause 2.8).
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.9.7 If you use the same PIN code for multiple cards, the unlimited
liability applies to each card that has been misused.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.9.8 You are not responsible for losses that occur after
&BANKNAVN. has been informed that the card is to be blocked. Nor
will you be held liable for losses if you have been unable to
block your card due to circumstances at &BANKNAVN..
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.9.9 If you are under 18 years of age, your liability for the misuse
of your card by others will be assessed according to provisions of
the Danish Guardianship Act and the regulations concerning the
compensation liability of minors. This means that the excess of DKK
1,100 does not apply and that the provisions concerning liability in
the Danish Act on Payment Services will only be applied if they
benefit you.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
