4. Processing and disclosure of personal data and information about
purchases etc.
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
:FED.
4.1. Processing and disclosure of information about name, address, phone
number, civil registration (CPR) number and company registration (CVR)
number
:SKRSLUT.
.br
&BANKNAVN. uses information about name, private address, phone
number and civil registration (CPR) number - for Corporate
cards, also corporate information including company
registration (CVR) number - when issuing cards and in its
ongoing administrative processes. The CPR number can be used in
connection with accessing address information from the Danish
Ministry of the Interior's Central Register of Addresses, and
for running checks in the Danish financial institutions' register
of cheque and card misusers. &BANKNAVN. may also use
the CPR and CVR numbers to provide legally required information
to public authorities about balances on accounts, any interest
charged etc.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
4.2. Processing and disclosure of other information
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The other information that the applicant/company provides, as well as
information collected from bank details, information from credit
information agencies and the like is used by &BANKNAVN. as the basis for
credit assessment on issuing cards, blocking cards and for ensuring
unique identification of the cardholder/company. Such information is also
used as necessary for completing payment transactions.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
4.3. Consumption data etc.
:SKRSLUT.
.br
When you use your card, a record is made of the card number, the total
transaction sum, the date of the transaction and the location where
the card was used. The payment recipient forwards this information to
&BANKNAVN. via NETS. This information is stored by the payment
recipient, NETS and &BANKNAVN., and it is used in bookkeeping, for
preparing invoices/account statements (including electronic account
statements and allowing the cardholder to view his/her consumption via
the Internet), and for subsequently correcting any errors.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The information mentioned above is only otherwise disclosed in cases
where such is required by legislation and/or if such is necessary for
the enforcement of law, or to prevent misuse of the card. In the case of
corporate cards, this information may be processed and disclosed to the
company to allow the company itself to process the data in various
management information systems.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
