Section 1. &ÅCONT
:SKRSLUT.
Children and young people under the age of 18 who are not married are
minors and thus legally incapable. Young people under the age of 18 who
are married will, however, be considered minors and thus legally
incapable if, on issuing the marriage licence, the state administration
has stipulated such.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Subsection 2 In the absence of any statement to the contrary, minors
themselves cannot take on obligations in legal transactions, nor may
they dispose of their own property.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Subsection 3 To the extent that no other specific agreement has been
reached, the guardians are to act on behalf of the minor in financial
matters.
.sp 5mm
