:FED.
Receipt
:SKRSLUT.
.br
When you use your card to make a purchase or withdraw cash, you
should always make sure to get a receipt. The receipt is to display
the date, the sum paid and a part of your card number. You should
check that the sum matches the amount you withdrew or paid, and that
the receipt features the correct date. You should keep the receipt
until you have checked that the correct sum has been debited from
your account. It may happen that you do not receive a receipt when
you use some self-service machines.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
