2.6. Reversing payments you have approved
:SKRSLUT.
.br
Once you have approved a payment, it cannot be revoked. In certain
situations, however, you may be able to reverse a payment - see below.
.sp 3mm
:FED.
If you did not know the final sum when approving the transaction.
:SKRSLUT.
.br
If you did not know the final sum when you approved the payment, and if
the sum subsequently debited from your account is significantly higher
than what you could reasonably have expected, you may be entitled to
reverse the payment. This may, for example, occur in connection with
renting a car or checking out from a hotel, when you have allowed the
business or hotel to debit your account for refuelling the vehicle or
restocking the mini-bar.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
You must contact &BANKNAVN. within eight weeks of the sum having been
withdrawn from your account if you believe that you are entitled to
reverse a payment for which you have not approved the final sum.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
